ENTRY            F0820   20260213   20260508   20260508       F108
SUBENT        F0820001   20260213   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                  8         17
TITLE      Elastic and inelastic scattering of identical heavy
           ions
AUTHOR     (H.Emling,R.Nowotny,D.Pelte,G.Schrieder,W.Weidenmeier)
INSTITUTE  (2GERHEI,2GERMPH)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,239,172,1975)
           (J,NP/A,211,600,1973)
FACILITY   (VDGT,2GERMPH)The EN and MP tandem Van de Graff
           generators.
REL-REF    (M,,H.Emling+,J,NP/A,211,600,1973)
DETECTOR   (PS) The detectors are mounted symmetrically to the
           beam axis at forward angles and are operated in
           coincidence. In the elastic scattering of identical
           particles the angle between the direction of the two
           scattered particles is 90. degr. For inelastic
           scattering this angle is less than 90. degr.
HISTORY    (20070403C)
           (20260213A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              17
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           20
SUBENT        F0820002   20260213   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                  9         30
REACTION   (6-C-12(6-C-12,EL)6-C-12,,DA)
INC-SOURCE The 12C beam was obtained from CO gas that decomposed
           and ionized in the hydrogen discharge of a
           duoplasmatron.
SAMPLE     12C target: 20 ug/cm2 self-supporting natural carbon
           foil.
MONITOR    (79-AU-197(6-C-12,EL)79-AU-197,,DA,,RTH) The angular
           distributions were normalized by the Rutherford cross
           section of gold measured with the monitor detector in
           order to obtain the differential cross sections. At
           bombarding energies below 11 MeV, the measured cross
           sections were adjusted to the Mott cross sections of
           the 12C-12C scattering. A gold target of 25 ug/cm2
           thickness was used.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) The 12C particles scattered from gold were
           detected with a silicon surface-barrier detector at
           an angle of 35. degr. with respect to the beam.
CORRECTION Corrections due to the change of the solid angle of
           the position-sensitive detector with scattering angle
           were taken into account.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The uncertainties in the absolute cross
           sections were estimated to be 10% for a scattering
           angle of 90 degr. This estimate is based on the
           accuracy of the normalization procedure between the
           different runs and the uncertainties in setting
           windows in the mass spectra.
STATUS     (CURVE,,H.Emling+,J,NP/A,211,600,1973) Fig.3 (left
           side). Same data presented on fig.2 at
           Nucl.Phys.,A239(1975)172.
HISTORY    (20260213A) SD: Data were re-digitized. BIB updated.
ENDBIB              30
COMMON               5          3
ANG-CM     EN-ERR-DIG ANG-ERR    DATA-ERR   ERR-DIG
ADEG       MEV        ADEG       PER-CENT   PER-CENT
        90.      0.039         2.        10.        1.5
ENDCOMMON            3
